  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Randomly assign patients with fractures of the proximal humerus to conservative treatment to&#xD;
      a group in which a control radiological study will be carried out after a week of evolution&#xD;
      of the fracture and to another group in which this control radiology will not be carried out.&#xD;
      In the evolutionary controls, it will be determined whether there are differences between the&#xD;
      two groups in the final functional result, in the perception of quality of life, and in the&#xD;
      number of complications derived from the fracture.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
